[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The enrollment function is doing four things in order. First, the eligibility check filters out patients the bot is not designed to serve (minors in adult-only deployments, primary psychotic-spectrum diagnoses, active inpatient treatment); these patients get a referral, not an enrollment. Second, the consent record captures the mental-health-specific consent including state-specific provisions; the consent has a version stamp that future support decisions reference. Third, the longitudinal store is initialized with the patient's preferences, the safety-plan-on-file flag, and (only with consent) the chart-derived diagnoses and medications. Fourth, the enrollment event flows out for population-health and per-cohort monitoring. Skipping any of these steps undercuts the discipline the rest of the architecture depends on.
