[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1904[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The receive-message step does seven things in order, and skipping any of them weakens a load-bearing piece of the architecture. The session bootstrap; the user-message persistence; the input-safety screening with mental-health-specific injection patterns; the continuous crisis screening that runs on every utterance regardless of conversation context; the sensitive-disclosure detection that records mandatory-reporting categories on a separately-keyed surface; the longitudinal-context load that brings in the safety plan, recent symptom tracking, and consent posture; and the disclosure-refresh that reinforces the bot-is-a-tool-not-a-friend boundary at session start and at periodic intervals. The order matters: crisis screening runs before any longitudinal-context load because a positive screen short-circuits the rest of the flow.
